o the threads","type":"comment"},{"color":{"a":1.0,"b":0.0,"g":0.0,"r":0.0,"type":"Color"},"name":"comment_13","node_position":{"x":3958.0,"y":248.0},"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"size":{"x":702.0,"y":338.0},"text":"","title":"Some final warping, adding an (optional) background","type":"comment"},{"color":{"a":1.0,"b":0.0,"g":0.0,"r":0.0,"type":"Color"},"name":"comment_14","node_position":{"x":5018.0,"y":248.0},"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"size":{"x":262.0,"y":218.0},"text":"","title":"Blending base gauze and wrinkles","type":"comment"},{"color":{"a":1.0,"b":0.0,"g":0.0,"r":0.0,"type":"Color"},"name":"comment_15","node_position":{"x":6620.0,"y":-120.0},"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"size":{"x":720.0,"y":920.0},"text":"NOTE: If you change the values in the nodes but not the remote, they won't match and the remote won't work properly. It's best to just change values in the remote only, for the associated nodes.\n\nNOTE: This doesn't have a randomization function (e.g. the Rips/Tears noise), so go to the corresponding node and click the dice icon. ","title":"Basic remote for the gauze","type":"comment"},{"color":{"a":1.0,"b":0.0,"g":0.0,"r":0.0,"type":"Color"},"name":"comment_16","node_position":{"x":7360.0,"y":160.0},"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"size":{"x":500.0,"y":460.0},"text":"Number of Threads = 300\nGradients = 150\nThread thickness = 1.00\nFray amount = 1000\nFray thickness = 0.004\nFray length = 0.004\nRips/Tears, noise X scale = 24\nRips/Tears, noise Y scale = 8\nRips/Tears, strength on horizantal threads = 1.69\nRips/Tears, strength on vertical threads = 2.792\nWrinkles intensity = 1.00\nWrinkles blur = 29.7\nBackground visibility = 0.14","title":"Example values (defaults)","type":"comment"},{"color":{"a":1.0,"b":0.0,"g":0.0,"r":0.0,"type":"Color"},"name":"comment_17","node_position":{"x":-1400.0,"y":320.0},"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"size":{"x":580.0,"y":320.0},"text":"NOTE: There is node all the way to the right, next to the material output node. That can simplify playing with certain values instead of hunting down the exact nodes.\n\nNOTE: If you change values in the individual nodes, and those values don't exactly match the ones in the remote, then the remote won't work properly. Change the values in the remote instead of the node, when possible. \n\n","title":"NOTE\": There is a remote","type":"comment"},{"color":{"a":1.0,"b":0.0,"g":0.0,"r":0.0,"type":"Color"},"name":"comment_18","node_position":{"x":278.0,"y":-1252.0},"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"size":{"x":1722.0,"y":438.0},"text":"","title":"Gradient generator, for the horizantal threads. This is overlayed on the base horizantal threads, which then makes it possible to blend the vertical and horizantal threads to weave them together. ","type":"comment"},{"color":{"a":1.0,"b":0.0,"g":0.0,"r":0.0,"type":"Color"},"name":"comment_19","node_position":{"x":278.0,"y":-712.0},"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"size":{"x":1762.0,"y":358.0},"text":"","title":"Gradient generator, for the vertical threads. This is overlayed on the base vertical threads, which then makes it possible to blend the vertical and horizantal threads to weave them together. ","type":"comment"}],"parameters":{},"seed_int":0,"shortdesc":"","type":"graph"}